      "content": "If you're feeling confident in your self-treatment, a few days of consistent use of high-quality lubricating drops is a good starting point. If the redness and discharge don't improve within 48 hours, or if the pain escalates, then you'll know it's time to call in the expert. Sometimes, a simple inflammation needs a strong dose of topical treatment to clear up fast.",
      "source": "target",
